# Notifications Module Rules

## Notification Entity

Notification for users.

## Notification Fields

- `id` - Unique identifier
- `userId` - User ID (foreign key to User)
- `type` - Notification type
- `title` - Title
- `message` - Message text
- `link` - Link to related resource (optional)
- `read` - Whether notification is read
- `createdAt` - Creation date

## Notification Types

- `new_proposal` - New proposal on request
- `proposal_accepted` - Proposal was accepted
- `proposal_rejected` - Proposal was rejected
- `new_message` - New message received
- `review_received` - Review received
- `achievement_unlocked` - Achievement unlocked
- `request_approved` - Request approved by admin
- `request_rejected` - Request rejected by admin

## Notification Endpoints

- `GET /api/notifications` - Get notifications (with filters)
- `PATCH /api/notifications/:id/read` - Mark as read
- `PATCH /api/notifications/read-all` - Mark all as read

## Notification Service

- Create notifications for events
- Deliver real-time via WebSocket or SSE
- Mark notifications as read
- Get unread count
- Support pagination

## Business Logic

Notifications are created when:
1. New proposal on request → notify buyer
2. Proposal accepted → notify seller
3. Proposal rejected → notify seller
4. New message → notify receiver
5. Review received → notify target user
6. Achievement unlocked → notify user
7. Request approved/rejected → notify buyer

## Real-time Delivery

- Use WebSocket or Server-Sent Events
- Emit notification events to connected users
- Store notifications in database for offline users
- Show notification badge with unread count
